{"title_page": "The Trap (1913 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1913 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Trap\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Edwin August]]\n| producer       = [[Pat Powers (businessman)|Pat Powers]]\n| writer         = \n| starring       = [[Murdock MacQuarrie]]<br />[[Pauline Bush (actress)|Pauline Bush]]<br />[[Lon Chaney]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = [[Universal Pictures|Universal Film Manufacturing Company]]\n| released       = {{film date|1913|10|3}}\n| runtime        = 1 reel\n| country        = United States \n| language       = Silent<br />English intertitles\n}}\n\n'''''The Trap''''' is a 1913 American [[silent film|silent]] [[short film|short]] [[drama film]] directed by [[Edwin August]], produced by [[Pat Powers (businessman)|Pat Powers]], and starring [[Murdock MacQuarrie]], [[Pauline Bush (actress)|Pauline Bush]] and [[Lon Chaney]]. The film is now considered [[lost film|lost]].<ref name=\"silentera\">{{cite web |url=http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/T/Trap1913.html |title=Silent Era: The Trap |accessdate=June 10, 2008|work=silentera}}</ref> Chaney would later appear in an unrelated film [[The Trap (1922 film)|of the same name]] in 1922.\n\n==Plot==\nLon is engaged to Jane, a social butterfly whose financial desires are impossible for him to fulfill.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0003474/|title=The Trap (1913) on IMDb|accessdate=May 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Murdock MacQuarrie]] as Chance\n* [[Pauline Bush (actress)|Pauline Bush]] as Jane\n* [[Cleo Madison]] as Cleo\n* [[Lon Chaney]] as Lon\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|id=0003474|title=The Trap}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Trap, The}}\n[[Category:1913 films]]\n[[Category:1913 drama films]]\n[[Category:1913 short films]]\n[[Category:American drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American silent short films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Edwin August]]\n[[Category:Lost American films]]\n[[Category:Universal Pictures short films]]\n[[Category:1913 lost films]]\n[[Category:Lost drama films]]\n\n\n{{1910s-short-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1913 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Trap\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Edwin August]]\n| producer       = [[Pat Powers (businessman)|Pat Powers]]\n| writer         = \n| starring       = [[Murdock MacQuarrie]]<br />[[Pauline Bush (actress)|Pauline Bush]]<br />[[Lon Chaney]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = [[Universal Pictures|Universal Film Manufacturing Company]]\n| released       = {{film date|1913|10|3}}\n| runtime        = 1 reel\n| country        = United States \n| language       = Silent<br />English intertitles\n}}\n\n'''''The Trap''''' is a 1913 American [[silent film|silent]] [[short film|short]] [[drama film]] directed by [[Edwin August]], produced by [[Pat Powers (businessman)|Pat Powers]], and starring [[Murdock MacQuarrie]], [[Pauline Bush (actress)|Pauline Bush]] and [[Lon Chaney]]. The film is now considered [[lost film|lost]].<ref name=\"silentera\">{{cite web |url=http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/T/Trap1913.html |title=Silent Era: The Trap |accessdate=June 10, 2008|work=silentera}}</ref> Chaney would later appear in an unrelated film [[The Trap (1922 film)|of the same name]] in 1922.\n\n==Plot==\nLon is engaged to Jane, a social butterfly whose financial desires are impossible for him to fulfill.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0003474/|title=The Trap (1913) on IMDb|accessdate=May 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Murdock MacQuarrie]] as Chance\n* [[Pauline Bush (actress)|Pauline Bush]] as Jane\n* [[Cleo Madison]] as Cleo\n* [[Lon Chaney]] as Lon\n\n==References==\n